<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to General
                            Wedemeyer</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d563</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">563</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/7–3047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to General
                            <persName type="to">Wedemeyer</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-30">30 July
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83136. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Wedemeyer</hi>: Thanks for 34. It is such a
                    clear picture of the situation that I have passed copies to the President,
                        Leahy,<note n="58" xml:id="d563fn1">Fleet Adm. William D. Leahy, Chief of
                        Staff to the Commander in Chief, President Truman.</note> Forrestal<note n="59" xml:id="d563fn2">James Forrestal, Secretary of the Navy.</note> and
                        Petersen.<note n="60" xml:id="d563fn3">Howard C. Petersen, Assistant
                        Secretary of War.</note> In the Department I have shown it to Lovett<note n="61" xml:id="d563fn4">Robert A. Lovett, Under Secretary of State.</note>
                    and Armour.<note n="62" xml:id="d563fn5">Norman Armour, Assistant Secretary of
                        State for Political Affairs.</note> I want you to know that your approach to
                    the problem has my complete approval. The situation appears most discouraging.
                    If you need anything from this end, please let me know.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
